# Project

The goal of the project is to build an MCP server for improving the quality of life of programmers.
Programmers can be overwhelmed by the productivity of their own when using the LLM agents.
They should take a break periodically for their health.
We implement a nudge to force the programmers to take a break by showing them a picture of a cat.
Cat. Yes, you will take a break when they show up.

## MCP Interface

The server has a single resource and two tools.

```
show_cat(int) -> image
```

show_cat is a tool to show a cat. 
A list of images of cats is stored in the cache locally.
The image of the given index (take mod if it is out of the index) is returned to the agent so that it is shown to the programmer.

```
add_cat(image) -> int
```

add_cat is a tool to add a cat image in the list of images. It returns the index of the added image.


## How to Develop

Write in Python using an official SDK using fast MCP class.
Put source files in src/ directory and tests in test/ directory.
Write a document of the code in docs for the overall design decisions and the design of each python file.

Always run a test using the test you implemented before finishing the task.

Whenever you make an update to the server, the server needs to be reloaded before it gets to effect.
Ask the user to restart the server.

